  "The entire circle": "",
  "The title of the chart": "",
  "A single slice of the pie representing one category": "",
  "The legend of the chart": "",
  "A sector (slice) is the wedge-shaped portion of the circle representing one category's share of the whole.": "",
  "What does 'central angle' mean in a pie chart?": "",
  "Always 90 degrees": "",
  "The angle at the center of the circle formed by the two radii of a slice": "",
  "The angle at the edge of the circle": "",
  "The average angle of all slices": "",
  "The central angle is the angle at the center of the circle between the two radii forming a slice, proportional to the category's share.": "",
