  "Company B has more market share, so 3D is appropriate": "",
  "3D charts are always more accurate": "",
  "The 3D perspective makes the front slice appear larger than its actual proportion": "",
  "3D effects create an optical illusion where slices in the foreground appear larger, potentially exaggerating that company's apparent market share.": "",
  "A school newspaper presents election results: Candidate A (32%), Candidate B (31%), Candidate C (22%), Candidate D (15%). Using a pie chart, it is very difficult to tell that Candidates A and B are only 1% apart. What graph would better show this small difference?": "",
  "A scatterplot": "",
  "A stem-and-leaf plot": "",
  "A boxplot": "",
